  "body": "As a user,\r\nI want to \"Sign in\" into the app using a different device\r\nSo that I can use my account on a different device\r\n\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWe should allow a user to restore their account on a different device and syncing all the data.\r\n\r\nThe backend should be already implemented, but might need some adjustments. \r\n@qfrank @Samyoul @siddarthkay have worked on it and will have all the knowledge necessary to help with the integration.\r\n\r\nWe don't need detailed errors when syncing for now, just a generic one is good enough to start with.\r\n\r\nThe task could be further split into multiple issues if necessary.\r\n\r\n### Designs\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/o4qG1bnFyuyFOvHQVGgeFY/Onboarding-for-Mobile?node-id=2917%3A381119&t=5Z1PPL195o1ec33Q-4\r\n\r\n### In scope\r\n\r\n- \"Sign in\" flow\r\n- Sign in by syncing flow\r\n- Scan QR\r\n\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n- Syncing devices screen (https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/15356)\r\n- Device sync complete screen (https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/15356)\r\n- Enable notifications screen - https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/15033\r\n- New splash screen - \r\n- I'm new to status flow\r\n- Swiping illustrations (we can show a single illustration to start with)\r\n- Terms of use\r\n- Getting started with status ( `i` icon on top right of the screen)\r\n- Enter sync code\r\n- \"I don't have status on another device\"\r\n- Find sync code\r\n- Different QR code invalid state\r\n- Preparing status screen\r\n\r\n### Definitions\r\n\r\n\"Sign in\" means restoring your account on a different device, and enable pairing between the two. For example I have an account on desktop, and I can \"sign-in\" on mobile, meaning I don't have the account on mobile, but I restore it from desktop, using the local pairing flow.\r\n",
